The most important distinction: these categories answer different questions

Category	Core question it answers
Data Structure	What shape is the input?
Pattern / Algorithm	What is the main solving engine?
Variation	Which subtype of that engine?
Composite Type	What second engine/helper is attached?
Canonical Link	Which prototype problem is this closest to?
Complexity	What time/space budget does it satisfy?

That is the cleanest separation.

⸻

Why people confuse them

Because they often collapse into one phrase.

Example:

“Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters”

You might casually say:

“It’s a sliding window hashmap string problem in O(N).”

But that sentence is actually mixing five different categories:
	•	Data Structure → String
	•	Pattern → Sliding Window
	•	Variation → Variable-size window
	•	Composite Type → + Hash Map / Hash Set
	•	Complexity → O(N)

That is exactly why these categories must be separated.

