10) The best wording style

Keep each line short.

Assumptions

Use noun-phrases:
	•	Sorted input
	•	Unweighted graph
	•	BST property
	•	Lowercase alphabet only

Edge cases

Use trigger phrases:
	•	n = 0
	•	single node
	•	duplicates
	•	all negatives
	•	target absent
	•	overflow risk

Invariant

Use one sentence:
	•	Window always valid
	•	Stack remains decreasing
	•	dp[i] is optimal for prefix i
	•	Queue contains current layer only

The invariant should be readable at a glance.

