11) Ownership / sharing notation

This is one of the most advanced but valuable layers.

When to use

Use when:
	•	nodes are reused, not copied
	•	objects point into existing storage
	•	multiple variables refer to same node
	•	buffer retains leftovers
	•	input is mutated in place

