	•	pointer/reference arrows instead of duplicate boxes
	•	one object, many labels referencing it
	•	“reused node” or “shared storage” tag
	•	no second copy box unless copied for real

Good examples
	•	linked list rewiring
	•	tree recursion
	•	in-place array marking
	•	LRU map entry pointing to list node
	•	substring by indices instead of copied substring

This makes memory diagrams much more accurate.

