15) Common mistakes in memory visualization

Mistake 1

Only writing Space = O(n) and not showing what the memory actually is.

Mistake 2

Confusing input memory with auxiliary memory.

Mistake 3

Ignoring temporary copies and rebuilds.

Mistake 4

Ignoring recursion stack.

Mistake 5

Not separating output-sized memory from helper memory.

Mistake 6

Drawing copies where the algorithm actually reuses existing nodes/arrays.

Mistake 7

Not showing peak simultaneous occupancy for containers.

