16) The universal memory template

Use this exact pattern:

Memory Panel

Input
	•	what is already present?

Aux
	•	what extra structures are allocated?

Temp
	•	what appears only briefly?

Output
	•	what must be stored as the answer?

Growth
	•	O(1) / O(n) / O(mn) / O(h) / O(output) / ...

Example:

Memory
Input: array nums
Aux: hash map of seen values
Temp: current scalar x
Output: pair of indices
Growth: Aux = O(n), Temp = O(1), Output = O(1)

That is the cleanest standard format.

