18) Final compression

If I compress the entire memory-visualization guide into one sentence:

Draw the input storage, the extra helper state, the temporary objects, and the output separately, then label which parts persist, which parts grow with input, and which parts are reused instead of copied.

That is the full guide to memory visualization.



