	•	DFS + memoization

3.8 State

What minimum information defines the live position of the machine.

Requirement:
Every optimized solution must have a state definition.

3.9 Invariant

What must remain true during operation.

Requirement:
Every optimized solution must have at least one core invariant.

3.10 Proof shape

What bounded-lifetime argument proves the complexity.

Requirement:
Every family must have a recognizable proof geometry:
	•	one sweep
	•	each pointer advances once
	•	each state solved once
	•	each element pushed/popped once
	•	range halves each step
	•	log-height path
	•	build once, query many

That is the ontology base.
