Part V — The deepest requirement of a pattern chapter

If I reduce everything to the single strongest requirement, it is this:

A chapter is only complete if it explains:

what naive search is doing, what exact repetition is wasteful, what hidden structural property allows compression, what minimal state replaces the repetition, what invariant protects that state, and what proof geometry bounds the resulting time and memory.

That is the deepest core.

Everything else is support structure.

