22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Use this mini decision tree to decide whether a new problem belongs here.

Q1

Is the object contiguous?
	•	no -> not sliding window
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Can I update the state by only:
	•	adding rightmost element
	•	removing leftmost element?
	•	no -> not plain window
	•	yes -> continue

Q3

Does a validity or score condition depend only on current window state?
	•	no -> suspect prefix sum / DP / other
	•	yes -> continue

Q4

Can left/right move monotonically without reset?
	•	no -> suspect another framework
	•	yes -> sliding window is likely valid

Q5

What subtype is it?
	•	exact size -> fixed-size
	•	longest valid -> variable-size valid
	•	shortest valid -> minimum-valid
	•	count exact-k -> often at-most decomposition
	•	need current max/min -> possibly window + deque

That is the operational diagnostic.

