26. Final deep compression of the family

The irreducible statement of sliding window is:

Sliding window is valid when a contiguous region can be represented by two monotone boundaries and a compact summary of its contents, so that overlapping brute-force windows collapse into one live window whose validity is maintained incrementally.

And the irreducible teaching statement is:

The learner has mastered sliding window only when they can name:
	•	the brute-force waste,
	•	the maintained state,
	•	the invariant,
	•	the subtype,
	•	and the exact reason the boundaries never need to reset.

That is the full gold-standard chapter for one family.

Next best family to build to the same standard is Binary Search or Dynamic Programming.



