23. Worked transformation recipes

⸻

Recipe A — Linear search in sorted array -> exact binary search

Brute force

Scan each value until target found.

Waste

Sequential probing of an ordered array.

Compression

Probe middle; comparison discards half.

Invariant

If target exists, it remains in surviving interval.

Canonical

Classic Binary Search

⸻

Recipe B — Find first bad version -> boundary search

Brute force

Check each version in order.

Waste

Testing all earlier versions one by one despite monotone validity.

Compression

Search the false/true boundary directly.

Invariant

First bad version remains in interval.

Canonical

First Bad Version / lower bound

⸻

Recipe C — Try every speed -> answer-space search

Brute force

Test speed 1, 2, 3, … until feasible.

Waste

Sequential candidate testing over monotone feasibility space.

Compression

Probe mid-speed, run checker, discard half of speed range.

Invariant

Minimum feasible speed remains in interval.

Canonical

Koko Eating Bananas

⸻

Recipe D — Search rotated array linearly -> structured-half binary search

Brute force

Scan all positions.

Waste

Ignoring the fact that each midpoint reveals one sorted half.

Compression

Identify sorted side, test whether target can lie there, discard impossible half.

Invariant

If target exists, it remains in the surviving interval.

Canonical

Search in Rotated Sorted Array

