21. Code-shape skeleton

A gold-standard chapter must explain code shape.

⸻

21.1 Memoization skeleton
	1.	define recursive function on state
	2.	base cases
	3.	memo lookup
	4.	compute recurrence from smaller states
	5.	store and return

This is often the cleanest bridge from brute force.

⸻

21.2 Tabulation skeleton
	1.	define state meaning
	2.	allocate table
	3.	initialize base states
	4.	fill in dependency-safe order
	5.	extract answer

This is the standard bottom-up skeleton.

⸻

21.3 Space-optimized skeleton
	1.	identify only needed previous states
	2.	replace full table with rolling variables/rows
	3.	update carefully in correct order

This is an advanced but essential pattern.

