22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Use this mini decision tree.

Q1

Can I define a compact state that fully determines the future?
	•	no -> not ready for DP
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Do the same states recur across different brute-force branches?
	•	no -> memoization may not help much
	•	yes -> continue

Q3

Can I write a recurrence/transition from smaller states?
	•	no -> DP not yet formed
	•	yes -> continue

Q4

Are the total number of states manageable?
	•	no -> may need optimization or another family
	•	yes -> DP likely valid

Q5

Which subtype?
	•	one index -> 1D DP
	•	two indices -> 2D sequence/grid DP
	•	capacity/sum -> knapsack style
	•	interval -> interval DP
	•	mask -> bitmask DP
	•	node/subtree -> tree DP
	•	digit position -> digit DP

That is the operational diagnostic.

