23. Worked transformation recipes

⸻

Recipe A — Fibonacci-style recursion -> 1D DP

Brute force

Recurse on f(n-1) and f(n-2) repeatedly.

Waste

Same f(k) recomputed many times.

Compression

Store dp[k].

Invariant

Once dp[k] is computed, it equals the exact answer for that subproblem.

Canonical

Climbing Stairs / Fibonacci

⸻

Recipe B — Pick/skip recursion -> 1D optimization DP

Brute force

At index i, either take item or skip it, recurse.

Waste

Same suffix/subproblem revisited.

Compression

Let dp[i] mean best answer from index/prefix i.

Canonical

House Robber

⸻

Recipe C — Coin recursion -> min-transition DP

Brute force

Try all coins recursively for remaining amount.

Waste

Same remaining amount solved many times.

Compression

Let dp[x] = min coins needed for amount x.

Canonical

Coin Change

⸻

Recipe D — Sequence alignment brute force -> 2D DP

Brute force

At (i, j), branch on matching/editing/skipping recursively.

Waste

Same suffix-pair (i, j) revisited repeatedly.

Compression

Store one answer per index pair.

Canonicals

LCS, Edit Distance

⸻

Recipe E — Subset exploration -> bitmask DP

Brute force

Try all subset states with repeated recomputation of partial sets.

Waste

Same chosen-subset configuration revisited.

Compression

Represent chosen set as mask, solve once per mask.

Canonical

TSP-like subset DP

⸻

