22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Use this mini decision tree.

Q1

Does brute force branch on many local choices?
	•	no -> maybe not greedy
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Is there a plausible local dominance rule?
	•	no -> likely not greedy
	•	yes -> continue

Q3

Can you prove a local choice is safe by exchange/dominance/frontier logic?
	•	no -> not yet greedy
	•	yes -> continue

Q4

What subtype is it?
	•	sort then choose -> sort-greedy
	•	cover/reach -> frontier greedy
	•	active pool of candidates -> heap-assisted greedy
	•	reset/discard impossible prefix -> deficit greedy
	•	build result symbol by symbol -> constructive greedy

That is the operational diagnostic.

