23. Worked transformation recipes

⸻

Recipe A — Try all interval subsets -> earliest-finish greedy

Brute force

Try many subsets/orders of non-overlapping intervals.

Waste

Exploring many branches that differ mainly in which compatible interval is chosen first.

Compression

Choose the interval with earliest finishing time.

Why safe

It leaves maximum room for future intervals.

Canonical

Activity Selection / Non-overlapping Intervals

⸻

Recipe B — Try all jump sequences -> frontier greedy

Brute force

Explore all reachable jump paths.

Waste

Many paths differ only in how far they extend the current reachable frontier.

Compression

Track the farthest reach achievable so far.

Why safe

A farther frontier dominates any weaker one.

Canonical

Jump Game

⸻

Recipe C — Try all starting stations -> deficit greedy

Brute force

Simulate the full route from every start.

Waste

Many failing prefixes are re-tested from internal starts that are already doomed.

Compression

When a prefix fails, discard all starts inside that failed segment.

Why safe

Any start inside a deficit segment inherits that deficit disadvantage.

Canonical

Gas Station

⸻

Recipe D — Repeatedly rescan active tasks -> heap-assisted greedy

Brute force

At each step, scan all active tasks/resources to choose the best one.

Waste

Repeated best-element search over changing active set.

Compression

Keep active candidates in a heap and choose the best current one greedily.

Canonical

Meeting Rooms II / scheduling variants

