23. Worked transformation recipes

⸻

Recipe A — DFS all paths -> shortest-path BFS

Brute force

Try many paths recursively until target found.

Waste

Longer paths explored before all shorter ones are exhausted.

Compression

Expand by distance layers.

Why safe

All edges cost 1, so layer number equals shortest distance.

Canonical

Unweighted shortest path

⸻

Recipe B — Run search from each source -> multi-source BFS

Brute force

Run separate search from every source to find nearest one.

Waste

Repeated traversal of same space.

Compression

Put all sources into queue at distance 0 simultaneously.

Why safe

BFS wavefront from all sources computes nearest-source distance in one pass.

Canonical

Rotting Oranges / 01 Matrix

⸻

Recipe C — Explore transformations in arbitrary order -> implicit-state BFS

Brute force

Try transformations recursively or blindly.

Waste

No distance order; many longer transformations explored before shorter ones.

Compression

Treat states as nodes in an implicit graph and BFS them.

Canonical

Word Ladder

