14. Confusion map

A gold-standard chapter must include what DFS is confused with.

⸻

14.1 DFS vs BFS

DFS

Best when:
	•	structural recursion
	•	subtree logic
	•	component exploration
	•	path existence
	•	exhaustive search / backtracking

BFS

Best when:
	•	shortest steps
	•	nearest source
	•	level order
	•	wavefront processes

Diagnostic

Ask:

Do I need depth-first structure, or distance-layer order?

⸻

14.2 DFS vs backtracking

DFS

General path/subtree exploration family.

Backtracking

DFS plus:
	•	explicit undo
	•	constraint-managed partial solution
	•	exhaustive enumeration/search

Diagnostic

Ask:

Am I just exploring structure, or am I building and undoing partial choices?

⸻

14.3 DFS vs DP

DFS

Explores one branch recursively.

DP

Stores repeated subproblems.

Diagnostic

