15. Failure modes

A real chapter must say how people break the family.

Failure 1 — No visited control in cyclic structure

Classic graph/grid bug.

Failure 2 — Using DFS for shortest-path objective

Most common conceptual mistake.

Failure 3 — Wrong return-value combination

Especially in subtree aggregation.

Failure 4 — Forgetting to undo in backtracking

Path/state contamination bug.

Failure 5 — Stack overflow / recursion-depth issues

Practical implementation failure.

Failure 6 — Carrying incorrect path state

Especially in path-sum and backtracking variants.

