22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Use this mini decision tree.

Q1

Is the structure naturally branchy/hierarchical?
	•	no -> DFS not automatic
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Do I need shortest distance/layer order?
	•	yes -> BFS likely better
	•	no -> continue

Q3

Do I need subtree/path exploration or exhaustive branch search?
	•	yes -> DFS likely valid
	•	no -> continue diagnostic with other families

Q4

Are cycles/revisits possible?
	•	yes -> need visited or parent control
	•	no -> plain tree-style DFS may work

Q5

Do repeated states occur?
	•	yes -> consider memoized DFS / DP
	•	no -> plain DFS/backtracking likely enough

That is the operational diagnostic.

