21. Code-shape skeleton

21.1 Opposite-end skeleton
	1.	initialize left and right
	2.	while left < right:
	•	inspect pair
	•	if found, return/update
	•	else move one side by safe rule

21.2 Same-direction skeleton
	1.	initialize read and write
	2.	for each read:
	•	if item should be kept/placed:
	•	write it
	•	advance write
	3.	output processed prefix

21.3 Fast/slow skeleton
	1.	initialize both pointers
	2.	while fast can advance:
	•	move slow once
	•	move fast twice
	3.	inspect meeting/middle condition

21.4 Merge skeleton
	1.	while both streams nonempty:
	•	choose smaller/current correct head
	•	append/use it
	•	advance chosen pointer
	2.	append remaining tail

