22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Q1

Is the core issue pair/boundary/compaction/merge/relative-motion?
	•	no -> maybe not Two Pointers
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Can pointer movement be monotone and meaningful?
	•	no -> not ready
	•	yes -> continue

Q3

What subtype is it?
	•	both ends inward -> opposite-end
	•	same direction -> read/write or slow/fast
	•	two ordered inputs -> merge
	•	symmetric around center -> center expansion

Q4

Is sortedness/order required or available?
	•	yes -> classic elimination/merge form
	•	no -> maybe sort first, or perhaps hashing is better

