14. Confusion map

⸻

14.1 Prefix State vs Sliding Window

Prefix State

Best when:
	•	interval fact comes from cumulative relation
	•	negative numbers may exist
	•	many intervals/queries are conceptually compared

Sliding Window

Best when:
	•	one live contiguous region can be updated incrementally by add/remove
	•	validity is maintained locally inside the active window

Diagnostic

Ask:

Is the main insight cumulative difference between boundaries, or live maintenance of one current interval?

⸻

14.2 Prefix State vs DP

Prefix State

Usually simple cumulative decomposition.

DP

Needed when many future subproblems depend on compact states with branching transitions.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Am I solving interval properties from cumulative history, or solving many recursive subproblems?

⸻

14.3 Prefix State vs Hashing

Hashing alone is not the cumulative engine.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Is the map storing raw items, or is it storing cumulative prefix states?

If the latter, primary family is often Prefix State with hashing helper.

⸻

14.4 Prefix State vs range structures

If updates are dynamic:
	•	prefix arrays often fail
	•	range structures may dominate

