15. Failure modes

Failure 1 — Wrong cumulative state

Most common conceptual failure.

Failure 2 — Forgetting empty prefix

Classic bug in subarray problems.

Failure 3 — Using plain prefix sums when updates are dynamic

Structural mismatch.

Failure 4 — Confusing interval relation

Difference/equality/mod relation may be wrong.

Failure 5 — Missing sign/value transformation

Some problems need values transformed before cumulative state is meaningful, e.g. 0 -> -1.

Failure 6 — Treating prefix state as only “sum”

Loses many important problems.

