21. Code-shape skeleton

21.1 Next-greater stack skeleton
	1.	initialize empty stack
	2.	scan sequence
	3.	while current resolves stack top, pop and finalize answer
	4.	push current index
	5.	finalize leftovers if needed

21.2 Previous-boundary stack skeleton
	1.	initialize empty stack
	2.	scan sequence
	3.	pop dominated elements
	4.	current answer derived from stack top
	5.	push current index

21.3 Window deque skeleton
	1.	initialize empty deque
	2.	for each index:
	•	expire out-of-window front
	•	pop dominated tail
	•	push current index
	•	once window full, answer is deque front

21.4 Histogram stack skeleton
	1.	scan bars with monotone stack
	2.	when smaller bar appears, pop taller bars and compute finalized widths
	3.	optional sentinel to flush remaining bars

