22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Q1

Is the brute-force waste repeated nearest-boundary or active-extremum scanning?
	•	no -> maybe not monotonic structure
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Can a stronger new candidate permanently dominate weaker old candidates?
	•	no -> not ready
	•	yes -> continue

Q3

What subtype is it?
	•	next/previous greater-smaller -> stack
	•	width/span by blocking boundary -> stack
	•	moving-window max/min -> deque
	•	contribution by nearest boundaries -> stack + span logic

That is the operational diagnostic.

