15. Failure modes

Failure 1 — Using heap when sort once is enough

Common overengineering.

Failure 2 — Wrong comparator

Fatal.

Failure 3 — Missing payload fields

Then popped item cannot be processed correctly.

Failure 4 — Ignoring stale entries

Common in Dijkstra-like or lazy-update problems.

Failure 5 — Confusing top-k maintenance with full ranking

Leads to unnecessary memory/time.

Failure 6 — Treating heap as fully sorted structure

It is not.

