21. Code-shape skeleton

21.1 Basic heap extraction skeleton
	1.	initialize heap with candidates
	2.	while heap not empty:
	•	pop best
	•	process it
	•	insert resulting new candidates if any

21.2 Fixed-size top-k skeleton
	1.	iterate through items
	2.	push into heap
	3.	if size exceeds k, pop worst-surviving element
	4.	result is heap contents/top depending on query

21.3 Merge-k-streams skeleton
	1.	push each nonempty stream head
	2.	while heap nonempty:
	•	pop smallest head
	•	append to output
	•	push its successor if present

21.4 Dijkstra-style skeleton
	1.	push source with priority 0
	2.	while heap nonempty:
	•	pop smallest tentative distance
	•	skip if stale if needed
	•	relax neighbors and push improved distances

