21. Code-shape skeleton

21.1 Include/Exclude skeleton
	1.	if at end/base, record answer
	2.	choose include branch
	3.	recurse
	4.	undo if needed
	5.	choose exclude branch
	6.	recurse

21.2 General choose/apply/undo skeleton
	1.	if complete, record/return
	2.	enumerate legal choices
	3.	for each choice:
	•	apply
	•	recurse
	•	undo

This is the canonical backtracking skeleton.

21.3 Constraint-tracker skeleton
	1.	if complete, record/return
	2.	for each candidate:
	•	if legal under trackers:
	•	update path + trackers
	•	recurse
	•	restore path + trackers

