22. Diagnostic decision tree for new problems

Q1

Is the problem naturally a tree of choices?
	•	no -> maybe not backtracking
	•	yes -> continue

Q2

Can I maintain a partial solution and reject bad prefixes early?
	•	no -> backtracking may degenerate to brute force
	•	yes -> continue

Q3

Do I need all/one valid constructions rather than a simple numeric DP value?
	•	yes -> backtracking likely valid
	•	no -> continue diagnostic with DP/greedy/etc.

Q4

Are repeated states common?
	•	yes -> consider memoized DFS / DP hybrid
	•	no -> plain backtracking likely fine

Q5

What subtype is it?
	•	include/exclude
	•	permutation
	•	target-sum/combination
	•	board placement
	•	path search
	•	duplicate-aware search

That is the operational diagnostic.

