23. Worked transformation recipes

⸻

Recipe A — generate all subsets then test -> include/exclude backtracking

Brute force

Generate every subset bluntly, validate late.

Waste

Many branches can already be classified while building them, or you want structured generation.

Compression

Build subset incrementally by include/exclude decisions.

Canonical

Subsets

⸻

Recipe B — generate all permutations blindly -> used[] backtracking

Brute force

Try all arrangements without disciplined path state.

Waste

No structured tracking of used choices.

Compression

Keep current prefix and used markers.

Canonical

Permutations

⸻

Recipe C — enumerate all combinations then test sum -> target-pruned backtracking

Brute force

Build all combinations, then check if target met.

Waste

Branches already exceeding target are continued uselessly.

Compression

Track remaining target and prune early.

Canonical

Combination Sum

⸻

Recipe D — enumerate all board states -> row-by-row placement with attack trackers

Brute force

Try every board configuration.

Waste

Boards with early conflicts are still fully constructed.

Compression

Place row by row and reject attack conflicts immediately.

Canonical

N-Queens

⸻

Recipe E — search all paths blindly in board -> path-valid backtracking

Brute force

Try many complete paths without guarding revisit/prefix mismatch.

Waste

Bad prefixes continued too far.

Compression

Track current path validity and visited cells, prune on mismatch.

Canonical

Word Search

