14. Confusion map

⸻

14.1 DSU vs DFS/BFS

DSU

Best when:
	•	many connectivity merges/queries
	•	only component membership matters
	•	merge-only dynamics

DFS/BFS

Best when:
	•	you need actual traversal
	•	path/distance/order matters
	•	one-time component discovery may be enough

Diagnostic

Ask:

Do I need to explore the graph, or only maintain who belongs with whom?

⸻

14.2 DSU vs graph shortest path

DSU is not for shortest path at all.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Is the question about being connected, or about how far / by what route?

⸻

14.3 DSU vs hashing/grouping

Hashing groups by direct key equivalence.
DSU groups by transitive connectivity/equivalence.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Is the relation directly key-based, or does it become connected through chains?

Accounts Merge is a classic example of needing transitive grouping, not just hash buckets.

⸻

14.4 DSU vs DP/state compression

DSU compresses connectivity classes, not recursive subproblems.

