16. Correctness proof shapes

⸻

16.1 Representative correctness proof

Default proof.

Structure
	•	each root represents one component
	•	parent chains end at root
	•	find returns root
	•	elements with same root are in same component

⸻

16.2 Union-preservation proof

Structure
	•	if roots differ, attaching one root to another merges two previously disjoint components
	•	no element loses membership
	•	new root represents union of both sets

⸻

16.3 Redundant-edge proof

For cycle detection.

Structure
	•	if two endpoints already have same representative, they are already connected
	•	adding the edge creates redundancy/cycle relation

⸻

16.4 Metadata proof

For augmented DSU.

Structure
	•	metadata is correct at roots before union
	•	combine root metadata correctly on merge
	•	therefore metadata remains correct for new merged component

