13. Canonical archetype library for Trie

⸻

Canonical 1 — Implement Trie

Why canonical

Pure insert/search/prefix operations.

What it teaches
	•	root-to-node prefix meaning
	•	terminal markers
	•	exact vs prefix distinction

This is the base trie canonical.

⸻

Canonical 2 — Word Search II

Why canonical

Trie + DFS/backtracking with prefix pruning.

What it teaches
	•	trie as search-space pruner
	•	current board path corresponds to current trie path
	•	absent prefix kills whole branch immediately

This is one of the most important trie canonicals in the whole atlas.

⸻

Canonical 3 — Maximum XOR of Two Numbers

Why canonical

Bitwise trie mutation.

What it teaches
	•	trie over bits
	•	greedy-ish bitwise traversal within a shared-prefix structure
	•	best opposite-bit search

This is the other major trie canonical.

