21. Code-shape skeleton

21.1 Insert skeleton
	1.	start at root
	2.	for each symbol:
	•	create child if missing
	•	move to child
	3.	mark terminal

21.2 Exact search skeleton
	1.	start at root
	2.	for each symbol:
	•	if missing child, fail
	•	else move to child
	3.	return whether final node terminal

21.3 Prefix search skeleton
	1.	start at root
	2.	follow prefix symbols
	3.	success if path exists fully

21.4 Trie + DFS skeleton
	1.	DFS builds current path
	2.	move through trie simultaneously
	3.	if trie child missing, prune
	4.	if trie node terminal, record word
	5.	continue neighbors
	6.	undo/backtrack

