14. Confusion map

⸻

14.1 Range Structures vs Prefix State

Prefix State

Best when:
	•	static data
	•	simple cumulative queries
	•	no dynamic updates
	•	answer derivable by two prefixes

Range Structures

Best when:
	•	many dynamic updates
	•	general interval combine operations
	•	nontrivial range decomposition

Diagnostic

Ask:

Can two prefixes solve this, or do I need a reusable hierarchical summary with updates?

⸻

14.2 Range Structures vs Heap

Heap

Maintains best active candidate.

Range Structures

Answer fixed indexed-range summaries.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Is the problem about interval aggregates or about current best among active candidates?

⸻

14.3 Segment Tree vs Sparse Table

Segment Tree

Dynamic updates supported.

Sparse Table

Static data, faster immutable queries.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Are updates allowed?

⸻

14.4 Range Structures vs DP

Range Structures

Store reusable summaries over domains.

DP

Stores answers to subproblems/states.

Some advanced problems mix both, but their roles differ.

