16. Correctness proof shapes

⸻

16.1 Summary-composition proof

Default proof.

Structure
	•	each stored summary is correct for its covered range
	•	combine rule is correct
	•	therefore larger range answers are correct

This is the family’s main proof grammar.

⸻

16.2 Range-decomposition proof

For queries.

Structure
	•	target query range decomposes into a bounded set of stored blocks
	•	combining those blocks yields the correct answer

⸻

16.3 Update-locality proof

For dynamic structures.

Structure
	•	only summaries whose ranges cover the updated point/range are affected
	•	updating those summaries restores global correctness

⸻

16.4 Doubling proof

For binary lifting.

Structure
	•	jump 2^k is composed from two jumps of 2^(k-1)
	•	therefore precomputed powers-of-two jumps are correct and composable

⸻

17. Complexity proof defaults

17.1 Log-height proof

For Fenwick / Segment Tree.

Each query or update touches only:
	•	O(log n) blocks/nodes

This is the main dynamic-range proof shape.

17.2 Preprocess once, query many

For sparse table / jump tables:
	•	preprocessing O(n log n)
	•	queries O(1) or O(log n)

17.3 Query block-count proof

A range is covered by only a bounded number of canonical blocks.

That is the family’s geometry.

