15. Failure modes

Failure 1 — Using BFS on weighted shortest path

Most common conceptual failure.

Failure 2 — Using Dijkstra with negative weights

Invalid.

Failure 3 — Missing extra state dimension

Classic failure in constrained-route problems.

Failure 4 — Treating topo sort as just “some ordering”

The zero-indegree readiness invariant is essential.

Failure 5 — Forgetting cycle handling in dependency problems

If a topo order cannot cover all nodes, cycle semantics matter.

Failure 6 — Confusing tentative value with finalized value

Especially in weighted shortest path.

