21. Code-shape skeleton

21.1 Dijkstra-style skeleton
	1.	initialize distances
	2.	push source into min-heap
	3.	while heap not empty:
	•	pop smallest tentative state
	•	skip stale if needed
	•	relax outgoing edges
	•	push improved neighbors

21.2 Topological-sort skeleton
	1.	compute indegrees
	2.	queue all zero-indegree nodes
	3.	while queue not empty:
	•	pop ready node
	•	append/process it
	•	decrement neighbors’ indegrees
	•	queue newly zero-indegree nodes

21.3 DAG-DP skeleton
	1.	compute topological order
	2.	initialize source/base values
	3.	process nodes in topo order
	4.	relax/propagate along outgoing edges

21.4 State-augmented graph skeleton
	1.	define expanded state
	2.	initialize frontier over expanded source states
	3.	run weighted/unweighted graph logic on expanded state space

