25. Final deep compression of the family

The irreducible statement of Graph Advanced is:

Graph Advanced is valid when the graph’s weights, dependencies, acyclicity, or extra state define a correctness-preserving processing order that collapses arbitrary path or order exploration into structured frontier or topological propagation.

And the irreducible teaching statement is:

The learner has mastered Graph Advanced only when they can name:
	•	the graph semantics,
	•	the correct processing order,
	•	the state carried at each node,
	•	the subtype,
	•	and why that order makes propagation or shortest-path logic correct.

