Failure 1 — Pattern spotting without proof

Most common conceptual failure.

Failure 2 — Wrong invariant

True but insufficient.

Failure 3 — Formula guessed from small examples

Dangerous.

Failure 4 — Hidden edge cases ignored

Overflow, sign, zero, negative values, modular normalization, etc.

Failure 5 — Using “math” as excuse to skip reasoning

Fatal for correctness.

