14. Confusion map

⸻

14.1 SQL / Relational vs Hashing / grouping in code

SQL / Relational

Uses declarative grouping/join semantics.

Hashing/code

Uses explicit maps and loops.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Is the problem fundamentally tabular and relational, so set transformations are the natural language?

⸻

14.2 SQL / Relational vs Window vs Group confusion

GROUP BY

Collapses rows into one row per group.

Window functions

Keep every row and attach analytics within its partition.

Diagnostic

Ask:

Do I want fewer rows or the same rows with extra per-partition metrics?

This is one of the most important distinctions.

⸻

14.3 SQL / Relational vs procedural thinking

Procedural

“Loop through rows.”

Relational

“Describe the relation I want.”

Diagnostic

Ask:

Can I define the target rows and their grouping/matching directly?

⸻

14.4 SQL / Relational vs Graph/recursive structure

If the problem is actually hierarchical search or pathfinding, plain relational SQL may not be the natural primary model unless recursive CTEs are explicitly intended.

