15. Failure modes

Failure 1 — Wrong join type

INNER vs LEFT is the classic bug.

Failure 2 — Wrong join key

Causes wrong matches or multiplicity explosion.

Failure 3 — Grouping at wrong grain

Aggregate computed over wrong row set.

Failure 4 — Using GROUP BY when a window function is needed

Collapses rows incorrectly.

Failure 5 — Using window function when aggregation is needed

Keeps too many rows.

Failure 6 — Filtering before vs after aggregation/window at wrong stage

Semantically wrong result.

Failure 7 — Ignoring duplicates / multiplicity

Relational algebra is very sensitive to row multiplicity.

