12. The three dimensions of practice

A real roadmap must say not just what to study, but how.

Every problem should be practiced in three dimensions:

Dimension A — Diagnosis

Before coding:
	•	world
	•	job
	•	brute-force object
	•	waste
	•	family
	•	impostors

Dimension B — Correctness

Before or during coding:
	•	invariant
	•	proof grammar
	•	why updates are safe

Dimension C — Visualization

After or during reasoning:
	•	choose drawing bucket
	•	show state evolution
	•	show memory/helper structure
	•	show final compression picture

Without all three dimensions, learning stays shallow.

