Final app schema to cover any question 


Here is the final app schema that can cover essentially any LeetCode question while staying consistent with your current React card system.

⸻

1. Core design principle

The app should be built in 3 layers:

Layer A — App Shell

Reusable React UI:
	•	layout
	•	tabs
	•	cards
	•	test-case switcher
	•	trace feed
	•	code viewer
	•	memory viewer

Layer B — Problem Schema

A single typed problem object that describes:
	•	the problem
	•	its brute force
	•	its optimized solution
	•	its visual language
	•	its traces
	•	its test cases

Layer C — Render Contract

A fixed set of sections that every problem can render, even if some are optional.

That gives you:
	•	one engine
	•	many problems
	•	stable visuals
	•	scalable generation

