Example A — House Robber

Story surface

A robber wants to rob houses on a street, but adjacent houses have alarms.

Translation
	•	houses -> array elements
	•	rob -> choose
	•	adjacent alarms -> adjacency restriction
	•	maximize loot -> maximize selected sum

Final structural sentence

“This is an array optimization problem: maximize the sum of chosen elements under the restriction that adjacent indices cannot both be chosen.”

That is the real problem.

