10. The 5 output forms of surface translation

A strong in-depth guide should say that surface translation can end in one of five forms.

Output Form 1 — Shape sentence

“This is really a graph problem.”

Output Form 2 — Mechanic sentence

“This is really a pair lookup problem.”

Output Form 3 — Constraint sentence

“This is really a choose-under-adjacency-restriction problem.”

Output Form 4 — Objective sentence

“This is really a minimum feasible threshold problem.”

Output Form 5 — Full structural sentence

“This is really a directed dependency graph problem where the goal is to determine whether a topological ordering exists.”

The last one is the best target.

