12. Common mistakes in surface translation

Mistake 1

Staying inside the story too long

Example:
thinking “robber” instead of “non-adjacent selection”

Mistake 2

Removing too much detail

Example:
saying “this is just an array problem” is too vague

Better:
“this is an array optimization with adjacency exclusion”

Mistake 3

Skipping the restriction

Example:
“this is a graph problem” is incomplete

Better:
“this is a directed dependency graph problem”

Mistake 4

Skipping the target

Example:
“this is a grid problem” is incomplete

Better:
“this is a grid connected-component counting problem”

