13. The universal final translation formula

For any LeetCode problem, the final translated sentence should look like:

“This is a [shape] problem about [mechanic] under [restriction], where the goal is to [target].”

Examples:
	•	“This is an array problem about pair lookup under distinct-index restriction, where the goal is to return original indices.”
	•	“This is a graph problem about dependency ordering under directed prerequisite constraints, where the goal is to determine feasibility.”
	•	“This is a grid problem about connected components under 4-direction adjacency, where the goal is to count regions.”
	•	“This is an interval problem about active overlap under time-range conflicts, where the goal is to minimize resource count.”
	•	“This is a numeric invariant problem about parity-preserving operations, where the goal is to determine reachability.”

This is the best universal surface-translation formula.

