Proper Dry Run Stack Methodology

A good dry run should not only say:
	•	“line 7 ran”
	•	“map became this”

It should show how execution moves, why it moves, and what state meaning changes.

So use this 8-layer dry-run stack.

1. Control-Flow Stack

Tracks runtime movement:
	•	function entry
	•	loop init
	•	loop condition
	•	body entry
	•	branch check
	•	branch taken / skipped
	•	increment
	•	return / exit

This answers:

why is this step running now?

⸻

2. Micro-Step Execution Stack

Break each line into executable subparts.

Example:

for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(nums.size()); ++i)

becomes:
	•	6(a) initialize i = 0
	•	6(b)(i) evaluate nums.size()
	•	6(b)(ii) cast to int
	•	6(b)(iii) compare i < size
	•	6(c) increment i

This answers:

what exactly inside the line executes first?

⸻

3. Expression Stack

For every expression, show:
	•	read operands
	•	compute result
	•	assign/store result

Example:

const int needed_value = target - current_value;

becomes:
	•	8(a) read target
	•	8(b) read current_value
	•	8(c) compute subtraction
	•	8(d) assign needed_value

This answers:

how was this value produced?

⸻

4. State Stack

Tracks named variables:
	•	i
	•	j
	•	current_value
	•	needed_value
	•	return value

This answers:

what is the current program state?

⸻

5. Memory Stack

Tracks containers and mutable memory:
	•	map contents
	•	arrays
	•	stacks / queues / heaps
	•	pointer targets

This answers:

what is stored outside scalar variables?

⸻

6. Semantic / Invariant Stack

Tracks what the state means.

Example for Q1:

before processing index i, the map contains all earlier values and their indices

This answers:

why is the current state trustworthy?

⸻

7. Decision Stack

Tracks points where the program chooses a path:
	•	condition true/false
	•	lookup hit/miss
	•	return/continue
	•	prune / no prune

This answers:

what decision was made here?

⸻

8. Exit Stack

Tracks what stops running:
	•	return exits function immediately
	•	loop increment does not happen after return
	•	next loop condition does not happen
	•	later lines are skipped

This answers:

what will not execute now?

