5. Monotonic stack / monotonic deque

Examples:
	•	Daily Temperatures
	•	Next Greater Element
	•	Largest Rectangle
	•	Sliding Window Maximum

Memory delta behavior
	•	medium to high mutation count
	•	push/pop heavy
	•	one step may trigger many pops
	•	memory changes are bursty, not smooth

Typical delta rhythm

Per iteration:
	•	compare current item to top/back
	•	pop all dominated items
	•	push current item
	•	maybe expire stale front

Typical deltas
	•	pop index 6 (dominated)
	•	pop index 5 (dominated)
	•	push index 7
	•	pop front index 2 (expired)

Signature
	•	bursty mutation
	•	stack/deque frontier churn
	•	many deltas in one step possible
	•	dominance-driven removals

Mental image

A frontier being pruned aggressively, then extended.

