Examples:
	•	Top K
	•	merge K lists
	•	heap scheduling
	•	Dijkstra frontier
	•	kth largest stream

Memory delta behavior
	•	medium mutation count
	•	push/pop centered
	•	frontier changes one item at a time, but may include stale cleanup
	•	mutations are ordered by priority, not locality

Typical delta rhythm

Per step:
	•	maybe push candidate
	•	maybe pop best/worst
	•	maybe discard stale top repeatedly

Typical deltas
	•	push (freq=5, value=7)
	•	pop min (freq=2, value=3)
	•	discard stale node

Signature
	•	priority-driven mutations
	•	frontier maintenance
	•	push/pop rhythm
	•	lazy invalidation sometimes present

Mental image

A ranked pool where top elements are constantly adjusted.

