Best compressed takeaway

Memory delta behavior is one of the strongest pattern signatures:
	•	scans -> scalar overwrites
	•	hashing -> sparse keyed inserts/updates
	•	sliding window -> oscillating grow/shrink deltas
	•	two pointers -> pointer motion with light memory
	•	monotonic deque/stack -> bursty pop/push churn
	•	heap -> priority push/pop churn
	•	BFS -> frontier + visited growth
	•	DFS -> recursion growth/shrink, light permanent marks
	•	backtracking -> choose / recurse / unchoose reversible deltas
	•	DP -> state-table writes
	•	graph advanced -> multi-structure relaxations
	•	DSU -> parent/rank rewrites
	•	design -> synchronized compound mutations

If you want, I’ll turn this into a master table with columns: pattern, delta rhythm, delta count, delta direction, delta reversibility, and visualization style.

Here is the master table.

Memory Delta Behavior Across Patterns

Pattern	Delta Rhythm	Delta Count	Delta Direction	Delta Reversibility	Typical Delta Types	What Usually Changes	Visualization Style
