Delta Count Legend

Count	Meaning
0	read-only step
1	single mutation
2	paired mutation
3–4	compound step
5+	burst / heavy structural churn

Delta Direction Legend

Direction	Meaning
overwrite	same slot changes value
grow	structure gains entries/nodes
shrink	structure loses entries/nodes
grow and shrink	active structure expands/contracts
prune then grow	dominated/stale items removed, new one inserted
improve	value updated to a better one
relink	pointers/ownership rewired

Delta Reversibility Legend

Type	Meaning
permanent	change stays
mostly permanent	may discard stale items later, but updates are forward-moving
reversible	explicitly undone later
stack reversible	call/path growth later unwinds
highly reversible	core algorithm depends on undo

Quick identification rules
	•	If memory mostly changes as scalar overwrites, think direct scan, simple DP, parser state.
	•	If memory changes as keyed inserts/updates, think hashing or prefix-count patterns.
	•	If memory expands and contracts around boundaries, think sliding window.
	•	If memory shows many pops followed by one push, think monotonic stack/deque.
	•	If memory shows frontier push/pop plus visited/dist updates, think BFS/graph.
	•	If memory shows choose + undo, think backtracking.
	•	If memory shows cell writes that never get undone, think DP.
	•	If one operation changes multiple structures together, think design/object-state.

