Now we define the actual delta vocabulary.

1. What a delta type is

A delta type is the exact kind of memory change that happens at one step.

Example:
	•	seen[2] = 0 is not just “memory changed”
	•	it is an insert
	•	or possibly an overwrite, depending on previous state

So delta typing should answer:
	•	what changed?
	•	how did it change?
	•	where did it change?
	•	what does that change mean?

