Example D — Course Schedule
	•	Objective: Decision
	•	Object: Directed graph
	•	Search space: dependency resolution / cycle structure
	•	Identity: node identity matters
	•	Order: prerequisite order matters
	•	Waste: repeated dependency traversal / hidden cycle ambiguity
	•	Fast operation: topo/DFS cycle state
	•	State: indegree or visitation colors
	•	Control: topo sort or DFS cycle detection
	•	Proof: acyclic dependency invariant

Final formulation

This is really a cycle-detection problem in a directed dependency graph, where the goal is to determine whether all nodes can be scheduled without violating prerequisites.

