14. Final master view for all LeetCode questions

All runtime growth across the LeetCode universe can be understood as one of these:
	•	scan growth
	•	ordered-search growth
	•	pair/tuple growth
	•	window growth
	•	frontier growth
	•	graph traversal growth
	•	state-table growth
	•	subset/state-space growth
	•	numeric-target pseudo-growth
	•	output-size growth

So the deepest final statement is:

Time complexity across all LeetCode questions is the study of how raw combinatorial growth is compressed into manageable event growth by structure, state, and invariants.

