17. The deepest universal statement about caching

Across all LeetCode questions, caching is really the answer to one question:

what information, if remembered now, prevents expensive work later?

That is the master principle.

Different problems answer it differently:
	•	remember seen values
	•	remember prefix aggregates
	•	remember current window counts
	•	remember solved subproblems
	•	remember visited nodes
	•	remember frontier candidates
	•	remember structure metadata
	•	remember API state

But the principle is the same.

