All about all type of approach in all leetcode question 



Here is the master map of all approach types across the LeetCode universe.

This is not just “hashing, DP, graph.”

This is a full structural view of the different ways a problem can be attacked.

A LeetCode question can be approached through one or more of these layers:
	•	brute-force approach
	•	structural approach
	•	optimization approach
	•	state approach
	•	control-flow approach
	•	proof approach
	•	implementation approach

So “all types of approach” means:

all major ways of converting a problem into a solvable algorithm.

⸻

1. The master families of approach

All LeetCode approaches can be grouped into these major families:

A. Exhaustive approaches

Search everything.

B. Incremental approaches

Build the answer step by step.

C. Cached/reuse approaches

Remember useful information.

D. Ordered approaches

Exploit sorting, monotonicity, or boundary rules.

E. Frontier approaches

Process only the active useful candidates.

F. Recursive decomposition approaches

Break the problem into smaller pieces.

G. Constraint-search approaches

Explore choices with pruning/undo.

H. Structural mutation approaches

Rewire or transform structure directly.

I. System/object-state approaches

Maintain synchronized state under operations.

J. Math/compression approaches

Use formula, algebra, combinatorics, or encoding.

These are the big families.

⸻

2. Exhaustive approaches

These are the “search everything” approaches.

