2.1 Brute force

Try all candidates directly.

Examples:
	•	all pairs
	•	all subarrays
	•	all substrings
	•	all paths
	•	all subsets
	•	all assignments

Use when:
	•	constraints are tiny
	•	needed as baseline
	•	needed to expose waste

Strength:
	•	simple
	•	correctness easy to reason about

Weakness:
	•	often too slow

Role:
	•	every strong solution should know what brute force is replacing

