Meaning

Use bounds to prune branches that can never beat the current best.

Examples
	•	optimization backtracking
	•	some combinatorial search problems

Strength
	•	stronger than raw backtracking
	•	can be dramatically faster in practice

Weakness
	•	bound must be strong to help much
