16. Two-pointers approach

Meaning

Use two moving indices to control a relation.

Common forms
	•	opposite ends
	•	slow/fast
	•	read/write
	•	partition pointers

Examples
	•	sorted Two Sum
	•	remove duplicates
	•	move zeroes
	•	merge-like scans
	•	linked-list cycle detection

Strength
	•	often O(n)
