22. Final compressed version

Iterative compute optimization across all 3872 LeetCode questions means:
	•	compute states in a legal loop/order
	•	compute each necessary state once
	•	avoid recomputation
	•	maintain state incrementally
	•	process only active/useful candidates
	•	compress memory
	•	reduce per-iteration work
	•	discard stale/dominated work early

The deepest version is:

turn the problem into explicit state progression where each iteration performs only information-preserving, future-useful computation.

