8. Practical “signals → protocol” map

If you see:
	•	pair/complement/seen before → hash protocol
	•	substring/subarray + constraint → sliding window
	•	sorted + pair/region logic → two pointers
	•	find smallest valid / monotone answer → binary search
	•	next greater / nearest smaller → monotonic stack
	•	window max/min → monotonic deque
	•	minimum steps in unweighted state graph → BFS
	•	component / subtree / recursive property → DFS
	•	prerequisite / ordering dependency → topo protocol
	•	overlapping subproblems → top-down or bottom-up DP
	•	generate all / choose-undo → backtracking
	•	local best seems globally safe → greedy
	•	repeated merges/connectivity → DSU
	•	prefix-heavy dictionary matching → trie
	•	repeated best-candidate extraction → heap
	•	implement fast mutable object → design/object-state

These are the major pattern-recognition protocols.

