11. DFS architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	tree, graph, grid, or recursive state space
Output:
	•	component info, subtree property, existence, aggregate, or traversal effect

Domain model

Solve or explore one branch deeply before returning.

State
	•	recursion stack or explicit stack
	•	visited when cycles possible
	•	return aggregates for recursive combine

Policy
	•	enter node/state
	•	recurse to children/neighbors
	•	combine local and child results

Execution engine
	•	recursive or stack-based depth-first control

Invariant

On return from a node/state, its subtree or reachable branch result is fully processed according to the defined meaning.

Main risks
	•	cycle handling
	•	recursion depth overflow
	•	wrong base case
	•	combining child results incorrectly

Extensions
	•	traversal only -> DP on tree/graph DAG
	•	existence -> counting/optimization
	•	recursive -> iterative stack simulation

