12. Topological / dependency architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	directed dependency graph
Output:
	•	valid ordering, cycle detection, or DAG-based computed results

Domain model

Items can only be processed once their prerequisites are satisfied.

State
	•	indegree or visitation colors
	•	queue/stack of ready nodes
	•	optional DP values on DAG

Policy
	•	discover dependency-free nodes
	•	process them
	•	release their dependents

Execution engine
	•	queue-based Kahn processing or DFS finish order

Invariant

Every emitted/processed node has had all required dependencies resolved.

Main risks
	•	forgetting disconnected DAG components
	•	cycle detection logic gaps
	•	indegree updates wrong

Extensions
	•	ordering only -> DAG DP
	•	cycle detection -> schedule feasibility -> weighted dependency optimization

