13. Greedy architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	usually set of candidates with objective and local selection rule
Output:
	•	feasible optimal or minimal/maximal result

Domain model

There exists a locally safe choice rule that can be applied repeatedly without backtracking.

State
	•	sorted candidates or current local summary
	•	minimal metadata needed to justify next choice

Policy
	•	pick locally safest/best candidate
	•	discard incompatible or dominated options
	•	continue without revisiting prior choices

Execution engine
	•	sorted scan or repeated local selection

Invariant

The partial solution remains extendable to an optimal full solution under the greedy-choice property.

Main risks
	•	choosing greedy when proof does not exist
	•	tie-breaking errors
	•	sorting by wrong key

Extensions
	•	static intervals -> resource allocation -> weighted / online variants
	•	greedy feasibility + binary search on answer

