14. Divide and conquer architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	recursively decomposable structure
Output:
	•	combined result from subparts

Domain model

Problem splits into smaller independent or semi-independent regions whose results can be merged.

State
	•	subproblem boundaries
	•	merge summaries

Policy
	•	divide
	•	solve halves
	•	combine

Execution engine
	•	recursion tree

Invariant

Each recursive call returns a correct summary for its exact subregion.

Main risks
	•	expensive combine step
	•	wrong merge semantics
	•	base cases too weak/too broad

Extensions
	•	divide and conquer DP optimizations in advanced settings
	•	tree-like recursive summaries

