15. Memoization architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	state-defined recursive problem
Output:
	•	answer for initial state

Domain model

The same recursive subproblem can recur from different branches.

State
	•	memo key representing subproblem
	•	cache from state -> answer

Policy
	•	if state already solved, reuse
	•	otherwise recurse to smaller states and cache result

Execution engine
	•	top-down recursion with memo lookup

Invariant

Cached value for a state is the correct answer for exactly that state.

Main risks
	•	incomplete state key
	•	oversized state key
	•	wrong sentinel/uncomputed marker
	•	hidden mutable context not included in state

Extensions
	•	sparse reachable states
	•	move to bottom-up if full state grid is easier

