16. Tabulation / bottom-up DP architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	problem with well-defined finite subproblem lattice
Output:
	•	final answer state

Domain model

Larger states can be built from smaller solved states in a legal order.

State
	•	DP table/array
	•	base rows/columns/scalars

Policy
	•	initialize base states
	•	fill transitions in dependency order

Execution engine
	•	nested loops / ordered fills

Invariant

Every state used on the right-hand side of a transition has already been computed correctly.

Main risks
	•	wrong state meaning
	•	wrong fill order
	•	bad base initialization
	•	overwriting dependencies when compressing memory

Extensions
	•	rolling arrays
	•	optimized transitions via prefix minima, deque, convexity-like patterns conceptually

