17. Backtracking architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	combinatorial search space with constraints
Output:
	•	all valid solutions, one valid solution, or best solution under pruning

Domain model

A partial solution can be extended step by step, and wrong branches can be abandoned.

State
	•	current path/placement
	•	used markers / constraint trackers
	•	optional best-so-far or memo of dead states

Policy
	•	choose option
	•	recurse
	•	undo
	•	optionally prune

Execution engine
	•	recursive search tree

Invariant

Mutable state matches exactly the current recursion branch and is restored after returning.

Main risks
	•	forgetting undo
	•	duplicate generation
	•	weak pruning
	•	expensive copying

Extensions
	•	add memo for repeated dead states
	•	upgrade to bitmask DP if overlap structure emerges

