18. Graph relaxation architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	weighted directed/undirected graph or weighted state graph
Output:
	•	shortest/optimal path values or best-known costs

Domain model

Costs improve through edges until no better improvement is possible under the chosen model.

State
	•	distance/cost array
	•	frontier structure (heap or iterations)
	•	optional parent reconstruction

Policy
	•	relax edge: try improving neighbor cost from current state
	•	repeat according to Dijkstra/Bellman-Ford/DAG order policy

Execution engine
	•	heap loop, repeated passes, or topo order

Invariant

Cost metadata means “best known so far” or “finalized optimal” depending on algorithm.

Main risks
	•	stale heap entries
	•	wrong infinity value
	•	overflow in cost accumulation
	•	using Dijkstra on negative edges

Extensions
	•	reconstruct actual path
	•	constrained shortest path with extra state dimensions

