19. DSU / Union-Find architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	repeated merges and connectivity/equivalence queries
Output:
	•	component answers, connectivity, or merged grouping

Domain model

Connectivity can be summarized by representative roots instead of repeated traversal.

State
	•	parent
	•	rank/size

Policy
	•	find representative
	•	union representatives
	•	answer queries through representative identity

Execution engine
	•	operation-by-operation merge/query loop

Invariant

Items in the same connected component share a representative root.

Main risks
	•	unioning non-roots
	•	forgetting path compression assignment
	•	size/rank maintenance errors

Extensions
	•	attach component metadata (size, weight, count)
	•	offline connectivity variants

