20. Trie architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	set of strings or prefix queries
Output:
	•	prefix existence, word existence, dictionary-guided search

Domain model

Strings share prefix structure that should be stored once.

State
	•	trie nodes
	•	children pointers/maps
	•	terminal flags

Policy
	•	traverse/create by characters
	•	branch only along existing prefixes

Execution engine
	•	iterative character traversal
	•	optional DFS over trie + board/search space

Invariant

Every trie path corresponds to a valid stored prefix.

Main risks
	•	prefix vs full-word confusion
	•	child indexing mistakes
	•	memory growth overlooked

Extensions
	•	word counts
	•	delete support
	•	compressed trie variants conceptually

