21. Linked-list / structural rewiring architecture

Contract

Input:
	•	linked structure
Output:
	•	modified linked structure, merged structure, cycle info, etc.

Domain model

Structure is defined by pointer relationships, so correctness depends on preserving reachability during mutation.

State
	•	current pointer
	•	previous pointer
	•	next saved pointer
	•	dummy head often

Policy
	•	preserve what will be lost
	•	rewire one local edge at a time
	•	maintain valid partial structure

Execution engine
	•	iterative pointer loop or staged split/reverse/merge passes

Invariant

Already processed portion of the list is valid and reachable in its intended new form.

Main risks
	•	losing node references
	•	creating cycles accidentally
	•	null dereference
	•	mishandling head/tail edges

Extensions
	•	singly -> doubly linked variants
	•	one-pass vs multi-pass rewiring

