Contract

Input:
	•	sequence of API operations
Output:
	•	per-operation results with time-complexity guarantees

Domain model

A persistent service object with internal synchronized data structures.

State
	•	primary store
	•	auxiliary indexing structures
	•	ordering structures
	•	counters / metadata

Policy

Each method call is a transaction:
	•	read/update internal state
	•	preserve complexity target
	•	preserve object invariants

Execution engine
	•	per-method local mutation flows

Invariant

All internal representations agree on the same logical object state.

Main risks
	•	partial updates leaving structures unsynchronized
	•	eviction/cleanup rules incomplete
	•	hidden O(n) scans breaking required complexity

Extensions
	•	LRU -> LFU
	•	add TTL
	•	add concurrency-like concerns conceptually
	•	add snapshots/history

