Q1. Two Sum

Core solved form

Find one pair of indices whose values sum to target.

Typical optimal:
	•	hash map
	•	one pass
	•	prefix cache

⸻

Extension 1 — Return all valid pairs

Change

Now answer is not one witness pair, but the full pair set.

What breaks

The original early return disappears.

Architecture change

System must support:
	•	duplicate handling
	•	pair deduplication
	•	full output accumulation

New state
	•	value frequency or value -> list of indices
	•	output set or dedup policy

New protocol
	•	hashing + accumulation
or
	•	sorting + two pointers + dedup

