15. The 6 most important operation semantics

Across all 3872 questions, these 6 matter the most:

1. Read without changing representation

Pure access

2. Update summary without changing shape

Scalar/map/DP writes

3. Change structure shape

Swap, rewire, merge, split

4. Schedule future work

Push/enqueue/heap insert

5. Finalize solved work

Memo write, DP write, output emit, visited/finalized mark

6. Revert temporary work

Undo/backtrack restore

These six explain most algorithmic behavior.

