The compact master formula

Every LeetCode solution can be described as:

Representation + Operation -> New Representation

Examples:
	•	freq[c]++ -> window multiset representation updated
	•	dist[v] = min(dist[v], dist[u] + w) -> tentative shortest-path representation improved
	•	curr->next = prev -> reversed-prefix linked-list representation extended
	•	dp[i][j] = ... -> solved-subproblem representation expanded
	•	q.push(v) -> future-frontier representation expanded
	•	path.pop_back() -> branch-local representation restored

