All types of step table for all 3872 leetcode question 


Here is the master framework of all types of step table for the full LeetCode universe.

A step table means:

a structured table that shows how a solution evolves step by step while state, representation, variables, and invariants change.

This is bigger than a dry run table.

Because different problem families need different kinds of step tables.

A good step table should answer:
	•	what unit is being processed now
	•	what code line / operation runs
	•	what state changes
	•	what representation looks like after the change
	•	what invariant is now true
	•	what next step becomes possible

So for all 3872 questions, the correct way is not one universal table shape, but a taxonomy of step-table types.

⸻

1. Why there are many step-table types

Different problems evolve differently.

Examples:
	•	Two Sum evolves by index scan + hashmap growth
	•	BFS evolves by frontier layers
	•	DP evolves by state fill order
	•	Backtracking evolves by choose / recurse / undo
	•	Linked list evolves by pointer rewiring
	•	Heap problems evolve by priority frontier changes
	•	Sliding window evolves by boundary movement
	•	Design questions evolve by operation stream and object state

So each one needs its own step-table architecture.

