All types of state figure table for all leetcode question 

Here is the master framework of all types of state figure table for the whole LeetCode universe.

A state figure table is different from a step table.
	•	A step table shows what happened at each step
	•	A state figure table shows what the internal state looks like

So state figure tables are about:
	•	representation
	•	memory shape
	•	active regions
	•	solved regions
	•	frontier structure
	•	pointer topology
	•	state fields
	•	invariants attached to the representation

This is one of the deepest visualization layers for all 3872 questions.

⸻

1. What a state figure table is

A state figure table is:

a table that captures the current internal representation of the algorithm at a given moment.

It answers:
	•	what state exists right now?
	•	how is it organized?
	•	which parts are active?
	•	which parts are solved?
	•	which parts are tentative?
	•	which parts are dead/stale?
	•	what does each field mean?

So instead of showing time-first, it shows structure-first.

⸻

2. Why many state figure table types exist

Different LeetCode families carry very different internal states.

Examples:
	•	Two Sum state is a prefix cache
	•	Sliding window state is an active interval + frequency model
	•	BFS state is a frontier queue + visited set
	•	DP state is a solved table region
	•	Linked-list state is a pointer topology
	•	DSU state is a representative forest
	•	LRU state is a synchronized object state

So there is no single universal state figure.

There is a taxonomy of state figure tables.

⸻

