All types of step figure table

Here is the full taxonomy of all types of step figure table.

A step figure table is broader than a normal step table.

It combines:
	•	step progression
	•	state snapshot
	•	representation view
	•	operation delta
	•	invariant/proof note

So a step figure table is:

a structured figure-table that shows how the algorithm evolves, what changes at each step, and what the internal state looks like after that change.

⸻

1. Master definition

A step figure table usually has some mix of these columns:
	•	step id
	•	active unit
	•	operation
	•	state before
	•	state after
	•	representation after
	•	invariant after
	•	output change
	•	next scheduled work

Different LeetCode families need different versions of that.

So the correct answer is a taxonomy, not one universal table.

