All types of trace tools


Here is the full taxonomy of trace tools for LeetCode.

A trace tool means:

any structured device used to observe, record, explain, verify, or debug how an algorithm evolves over time, state, memory, control flow, or representation.

So “trace tools” is broader than:
	•	dry runs
	•	step tables
	•	state tables
	•	debug logs

It includes every formal way to trace computation.

⸻

1. The master definition

A trace tool answers at least one of these:
	•	what happened?
	•	in what order?
	•	what changed?
	•	what stayed true?
	•	what is active now?
	•	what got discarded?
	•	what got revisited?
	•	what is the current frontier?
	•	what is the current memory state?
	•	why was this branch chosen?
	•	why is the answer correct?

