4. The 8 delta types you should always watch

For all LeetCode questions, almost every live change is one of these:

1. value delta

A scalar changed.
Example:
	•	best
	•	sum
	•	carry
	•	dist[v]

2. boundary delta

A boundary moved.
Example:
	•	left++
	•	right--
	•	low = mid + 1

3. membership delta

Something entered or left the active set.
Example:
	•	item inserted into map/set
	•	visited mark added
	•	frequency became zero

4. frontier delta

Future work changed.
Example:
	•	queue push/pop
	•	heap push/pop
	•	stack push/pop

5. topology delta

Shape changed.
Example:
	•	linked-list rewiring
	•	tree pointer change
	•	union of DSU components

6. solved-state delta

A state became finalized.
Example:
	•	dp[i][j] written
	•	memo state cached
	•	Dijkstra node finalized

7. branch delta

A choice path was selected or pruned.
Example:
	•	recurse
	•	skip
	•	prune
	•	undo

8. output delta

The answer being built changed.
Example:
	•	append to result
	•	attach node
	•	reconstruct path step

