12. The universal transformation questions

For any LeetCode problem, ask:

1. What is the raw representation?

How is the question originally phrased?

2. What is the computational representation?

What object really matters:
	•	pair
	•	interval
	•	subset
	•	path
	•	state
	•	component
	•	subtree

3. What memory representation will hold that object?
	•	array
	•	map
	•	set
	•	stack
	•	queue
	•	heap
	•	DP table
	•	bitmask
	•	pointers

4. Can one representation be converted into another?

That is usually where optimization happens.

5. What invariant defines the memory representation?

What must it mean at all times?

This is the master reasoning protocol.

