14. Final master summary

So the full answer is:

A. Any LeetCode question has representations at multiple levels:
	•	surface
	•	structural
	•	search-space
	•	state-space
	•	memory
	•	pattern
	•	invariant

B. Any data structure has multiple meanings:
	•	physical memory form
	•	logical abstract form
	•	operational form
	•	semantic role in algorithm

C. Any pattern has a memory signature:
	•	two pointers -> boundaries
	•	BFS -> queue frontier
	•	DP -> solved state table
	•	backtracking -> partial path + undo state
	•	heap -> priority frontier

D. Solving often means representing one thing in another form:
