18. Matrix complexity patterns

A lot of matrix questions start at:
	•	O(rows * cols)

That is the baseline full scan.

Then common escalations or optimizations are:
	•	O(RC4) still effectively O(R*C) for constant neighbors
	•	O(RClog(R*C)) if heap used
	•	O(RCC) for naive rectangle logic
	•	optimized to O(RC) or O(RC*something smaller)

Common sources of extra cost:
	•	exploring every rectangle
	•	rescanning rows/cols repeatedly
	•	revisiting cells without visited control
	•	expensive copying of submatrices

19. Common matrix bugs

These are extremely common across LeetCode.

Bounds mistakes
	•	row/col confusion
	•	negative indices
	•	using wrong dimension variable

Direction mistakes
	•	wrong neighbor offsets
	•	forgetting diagonals or adding them incorrectly

Mutation mistakes
	•	modifying original matrix when later needed unchanged
	•	visited marking collides with legal values

DP order mistakes
	•	using unsolved neighbors
	•	wrong fill direction

Shape mistakes
	•	assuming square matrix when rectangular
	•	transpose/rotate formulas only valid for square case

Region mistakes
	•	rectangle formulas off by one
	•	prefix-sum inclusion-exclusion errors

BFS/DFS mistakes
	•	visited marked too late
	•	queue seeded incorrectly
	•	multiple-source initialization wrong

20. Matrix representation conversions you should know

This is one of the most important sections.

Matrix -> graph

For traversal/path/connectivity.

Matrix -> DP table

When each coordinate is a solvable state.

Matrix -> prefix matrix

For fast rectangle queries.

Matrix -> histogram

For maximal rectangle.

Matrix -> flattened 1D ids

For DSU and compact storage.

Matrix -> ring layers

For spiral/boundary tasks.

Matrix -> coordinate transform system

For rotations/reflections.

