15. Example: reverse linked list

Original representation

A -> B -> C -> null

Desired representation

C -> B -> A -> null

Intermediate topology view

reversed prefix <- curr -> unreversed suffix

More explicitly:

null <- A    B -> C -> null
       ^     ^
      prev  curr

Then:

null <- A <- B    C -> null
            ^     ^
           prev  curr

This is pure linked representation reasoning.

