2. What “runtime stack changes” means

The runtime stack changes differently depending on problem family.

In iterative problems

Stack usually changes only by:
	•	function entry
	•	maybe helper call
	•	loop variables updating inside one frame

In recursive problems

Stack changes by:
	•	pushing new call frames
	•	holding suspended parent states
	•	returning and collapsing

In design/API problems

Stack changes per API call, usually shallow unless helper recursion exists

In BFS/DFS iterative versions

Runtime stack stays shallow, but logical frontier changes a lot

So for LeetCode, you should separate:
	•	runtime stack
	•	logical problem stack/frontier

These are often different.

