24. Interview explanation

I treat the problem as a complement-lookup problem instead of an all-pairs search problem. I scan the array once from left to right, compute the complement needed for the current value, and check whether that complement has already appeared. I store previously seen values in a hash map from value to index. The invariant is that before processing index i, the map summarizes the processed prefix only. When the complement is found, I return the earlier stored index and the current index immediately.

