25. Interview explanation

I treat each list as a reverse-order digit stream and simulate elementary-school addition one place at a time. At each step I read the current digit from each list, or 0 if a list is already exhausted, add them with the carry, create one output digit node from sum % 10, and propagate the new carry using sum / 10. I use a dummy head and tail pointer to build the result list cleanly. The invariant is that the result list built so far already represents the correct lower-order digits of the final sum.

